{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Behold, my eye has seen all this. My ear has heard and understood it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "What you know, I know also. I am not inferior to you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Surely I would speak to the Almighty. I desire to reason with God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But you are forgers of lies. You are all physicians of no value."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Oh that you would be completely silent! Then you would be wise."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Hear now my reasoning. Listen to the pleadings of my lips."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Will you speak unrighteously for God, and talk deceitfully for him?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Will you show partiality to him? Will you contend for God?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Is it good that he should search you out? Or as one deceives a man, will you deceive him?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He will surely reprove youif you secretly show partiality."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Won’t his majesty make you afraid and his dread fall on you?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Your memorable sayings are proverbs of ashes. Your defenses are defenses of clay."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Be silent! Leave me alone, that I may speak."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let come on me what will."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Why should I take my flesh in my teeth, and put my life in my hand?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Behold, he will kill me. I have no hope."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Nevertheless, I will maintain my ways before him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "This also will be my salvation, that a godless man will not come before him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Listen carefully to my speech. Let my declaration be in your ears."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "See now, I have set my cause in order. I know that I am righteous."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who is he who will contend with me? For then I would hold my peace and give up the spirit."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Only don’t do two things to me, then I will not hide myself from your face:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "withdraw your hand far from me, and don’t let your terror make me afraid."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then call, and I will answer, or let me speak, and you answer me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "How many are my iniquities and sins? Make me know my disobedience and my sin."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Why do you hide your face, and consider me your enemy?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Will you harass a driven leaf? Will you pursue the dry stubble?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For you write bitter things against me, and make me inherit the iniquities of my youth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You also put my feet in the stocks, and mark all my paths."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You set a bound to the soles of my feet,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "though I am decaying like a rotten thing, like a garment that is moth-eaten."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}